HEADWORD: Elaiometer
<hw>E`lai*om"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ olive
oil, oil + <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An
apparatus for determining the amount of oil contained in any substance,
or for ascertaining the degree of purity of oil.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

